            <title>[CAMEL-315] Unclosed InputStreams cause FileConsumer to hang on Windows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-315</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FtpProducer/SftpProducer get their &quot;In&quot; Message bodies as InputStreams, which they then neglect to close.  This appears to cause a problem in Windows where Files that are processed in this manner have an exclusive lock placed upon them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For more info, see this discussion thread: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/From-file-to-ftp-td14921828s22882.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/From-file-to-ftp-td14921828s22882.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
